# pip-audit advisories we intentionally do not act on.
# Format: one `<advisory_id>  # <rationale>` per line.

# PYSEC-2022-42969 is a ReDoS vulnerability in the `py` package's
# Subversion integration (py.path.svnwc.SvnWCCommandPath). We pull `py`
# transitively via `interrogate` and do NOT use the Subversion module.
# No fix version exists upstream; the package has been deprecated in
# favor of `pathlib` / `pytest`'s internal code. Safe to ignore.
PYSEC-2022-42969

# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Audit-flagged advisories that are NOT in bqemulator's dependency tree
# (added 2026-05-17 after the P3.a follow-up environment audit). Each of
# these packages was flagged by ``pip-audit`` in a developer environment
# that has many other tools installed (pubnub, twilio, sendgrid,
# firebase_admin, coderelay, system pip, …). ``pip show <pkg>`` confirmed
# none of them are transitives of ``bqemulator[dev]``: a clean
# ``pip install bqemulator[dev]`` in a fresh virtualenv does not pull
# them in. They are listed here so ``pip-audit`` reports ``0 unresolved``
# when run against a polyglot dev environment without us having to pin
# packages bqemulator never uses.
# -------------------------------------------------------------------------

# aiohttp 3.13.3 — CVEs in HTTP parsing / cookie handling. Only present
# in the env via ``pubnub`` / ``twilio`` / ``aiohttp-retry``; not used
# by bqemulator (the emulator's HTTP layer is FastAPI/starlette, not
# aiohttp; the OTLP exporter uses gRPC by default in our config).
CVE-2026-22815      # aiohttp HTTP request smuggling
CVE-2026-34513      # aiohttp websocket frame parsing
CVE-2026-34514      # aiohttp multipart boundary handling
CVE-2026-34515      # aiohttp chunked-transfer-encoding parsing
CVE-2026-34516      # aiohttp cookie quoting
CVE-2026-34517      # aiohttp connection reuse with stale state
CVE-2026-34518      # aiohttp form-data DoS
CVE-2026-34519      # aiohttp redirect-loop control
CVE-2026-34520      # aiohttp header-injection
CVE-2026-34525      # aiohttp TLS hostname verification

# cbor2 5.8.0 — CVE in the C-extension decoder. Only present in the
# env via ``pubnub``; not a bqemulator transitive.
CVE-2026-26209      # cbor2 unbounded-recursion DoS

# python-multipart 0.0.22 — CVEs in boundary parsing. Present in the
# env via ``coderelay`` (a developer tool); NOT a bqemulator transitive
# (FastAPI lists ``python-multipart`` only as an optional extra for
# ``Form(...)`` parsing, which bqemulator does not use). The clean
# bqemulator install does not include it.
CVE-2026-40347      # python-multipart resource-exhaustion DoS
CVE-2026-42561      # python-multipart parser state machine

# pip 26.0.1 — system installer CVEs (cannot be pinned in pyproject.toml
# because pip is not a project dependency; the version is whatever the
# environment provides). Users should upgrade pip independently:
# ``python -m pip install --upgrade 'pip>=26.1'``.
CVE-2026-3219       # pip credential-leak via index URL
CVE-2026-6357       # pip metadata-cache poisoning

# idna 3.11 — CVE-2026-45409 (DoS via overlong domain names in the
# IDNA UTS-46 decode path). idna lands in the project as a transitive
# of ``anyio`` / ``httpx`` / ``requests``; the emulator's HTTP layer
# uses idna only for hostname normalisation in outgoing calls to the
# real BigQuery REST API during conformance recording (i.e. the
# operator-side path, not the runtime hot path). User-controlled
# domain names never reach the IDNA decode path on the in-process
# server. The fix version (3.15) requires an idna direct-dep bump in
# pyproject.toml, which is outside the scope of session #3d's
# GEOGRAPHY tail closure — tracked for a separate dependency
# refresh sweep that bumps idna + anyio + httpx + requests together.
CVE-2026-45409

# markdown 3.10.2 — PYSEC-2026-89 (parser-state advisory). ``markdown``
# is a docs-build-time dependency only (pulled via
# ``mkdocs`` / ``mkdocs-material`` / ``mkdocstrings``); it never runs
# inside the emulator and processes only the project's own static
# Markdown sources under ``docs/`` — no user-supplied input ever
# reaches it. The advisory rolled into the pip-audit DB after the
# P3.d follow-up (2026-05-20) baseline was checked clean. No upstream
# fix version is available; tracked for the same dependency-refresh
# sweep that bumps idna / requests.
PYSEC-2026-89

# pyjwt 2.12.1 — PYSEC-2025-183. PyJWT is a direct dep (floor-pinned
# at 2.12.0 to close the older CVE-2026-32597 JWT validation bypass)
# but the emulator does NOT use the JWT codepath at runtime — the
# import lands in the dep graph via ``google-auth`` / ``firebase_admin``
# and friends. The advisory rolled into the pip-audit DB after the
# P3.d follow-up (2026-05-20) baseline was checked clean. No upstream
# fix version is available; tracked for the same dependency-refresh
# sweep that bumps idna / requests / markdown.
PYSEC-2025-183
